# hotgrin — rules for Cursor

This project uses hotgrin (.hot files), a 2026 language NOT in your training
data. Never guess hotgrin syntax from other languages.

Before writing any hotgrin code, read docs/ai-prompt-pack.md in this repo —
it is the complete spec, written for AI assistants, with a GOTCHAS list of
the exact mistakes AI models make.

The three most-violated rules:
1. ask always returns TEXT; numeric input uses: input n as whole default 5
2. Fallible calls (std/data, std/web, any action with give back problem)
   must be inside try ... if it fails ... end try — as the WHOLE value.
3. Every block closes explicitly: end if / end repeat / end action /
   end describe / end try / end test / end at the same time / end go.

Verify with the CLI, never by eyeballing: hotgrin check file.hot
